<h2>Common Mistakes That Kill Website Traffic</h2>
<p><strong>Publishing without keyword research.</strong> Writing about topics nobody searches for produces content that nobody finds. Every page needs a target keyword with verified search volume.</p>
<p><strong>Ignoring mobile optimization.</strong> Mobile devices account for <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/website-traffic-statistics/">63 to 70% of all web traffic</a>. A site that loads slowly or looks broken on mobile loses the majority of potential visitors.</p>
<p><strong>Chasing vanity metrics.</strong> Pageviews without conversions mean nothing. 10,000 visitors who bounce immediately are worth less than 500 visitors who engage and convert.</p>
<p><strong>Giving up too early.</strong> SEO takes 60 to 90 days for initial results. Content compounds over 6 to 12 months. Most businesses quit at week 4. The ones that persist for 6 months see the traffic curve inflect upward.</p>
<p><strong>Relying on one channel.</strong> 59% of websites lost traffic in 2025. Many of those sites depended entirely on Google organic search. Diversify across at least 3 to 4 channels.</p>
<p><strong>Publishing thin content.</strong> A 300-word blog post will not rank for anything competitive. The average first-page result on Google contains 1,447 words. Depth matters.</p>
